{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8e04d631-bd39-46d6-a439-69de68199d5a","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, simply **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n**Before:**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**After:**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- UseVSTest removed — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nMSTest.Sdk **3.4+** uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default, so removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is all that's needed.\n\n### Key behavioral differences to be aware of:\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Run tests** | `dotnet test` still works, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) |\n| **CLI options** | VSTest switches like `--filter` change to `--filter` with a slightly different syntax; use `-- --help` to see new options |\n| **`.runsettings`** | Still supported, but platform-specific config uses `testconfig.json` or CLI args |\n| **Code coverage / loggers** | You may need the new extensions (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`) instead of VSTest adapters |\n\nAfter the change, run `dotnet test` to verify everything builds and passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9d15e527-cfea-4e49-bca0-4aeba70c7526","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. Let me just answer from my knowledge about MSTest.Sdk migration from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":419,"requestId":"342E:362770:70DBB7C:7D36CC4:69F3FADB"},"id":"62c9a826-09a7-4f69-b176-b7e866d2fb56","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:59:18.332Z","parentId":"db0174c9-a595-4b3b-bfde-c2ccb37b5de6"}
